    "The earliest networks helpful for bioinformatics implementation were layers of neurons arranged in this straightforward manner; these layers are sometimes referred to as \"multilayer perceptrons.\"",
    "Feed Forward Neural NetworksThe earliest and most fundamental model of a neuron is the perceptron.",
    "A group of inputs are taken, added, and then an activation function is applied before sending the results to the output layer.",
    "A fundamental class of neural networks is called a feed forward neural network (FFNN).",
    "The intermediate levels are buried, with the input layer at the top and the output layer at the bottom."
